          "answer": "True",
          "explanation": "Private companies are now playing a significant role in developing space technology and offering commercial spaceflights."
        },
        {
          "question": "Has a permanent base been established on Mars?",
          "options": ["True", "False"],
          "answer": "False",
          "explanation": "While scientists are exploring the possibility of establishing bases on Mars, no permanent base currently exists."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "sentenceFrames",
      "title": "Sentence Practice",
      "frames": [
        {
          "pattern": "I think that _____ is important because _____.",
          "examples": [
            "I think that space exploration is important because it expands our knowledge of the universe.",
            "I think that technology is important because it makes space travel possible."
          ],
          "usageNotes": "Use this pattern to express your opinion about the importance of something.  Provide a reason to support your opinion.",
          "teachingTips": "Have students practice this pattern with different vocabulary words related to space travel. Encourage them to elaborate on their reasons.",
          "difficultyLevel": "intermediate",
          "grammarFocus": "Expressing opinions, using subordinate clauses",
          "communicativeFunction": "Giving reasons"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "If I were an astronaut, I would _____.",
          "examples": [
            "If I were an astronaut, I would explore the Moon.",
            "If I were an astronaut, I would conduct experiments in zero gravity."
          ],
          "usageNotes": "Use this pattern to talk about hypothetical situations related to space travel. Use the conditional to express what you would do in a specific scenario.",
          "teachingTips": "Encourage students to be creative and imaginative with their responses.  Ask follow-up questions to elicit more details.",
          "difficultyLevel": "intermediate",
          "grammarFocus": "Conditional sentences (second conditional)",
          "communicativeFunction": "Hypothesizing"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "discussion",
      "title": "Discussion Questions",
      "questions": [
        {
          "paragraphContext": "Imagine a future where space travel is as common as air travel is today.  People commute to orbital hotels, take weekend trips to the Moon, and even relocate to Mars.  This seemingly fantastical scenario might be closer than we think, as private companies invest heavily in space tourism and colonization efforts.  How would this accessibility change our perception of space and our place in the universe?",
          "question": "If space travel became commonplace, how do you think it would impact our society and culture?",
          "imagePrompt": "A futuristic cityscape with flying cars and spaceships taking off and landing, showing a busy spaceport with people boarding and disembarking spacecraft. No text or words should appear in the image."
        },
        {
          "paragraphContext": "The exploration of space has always been driven by a thirst for knowledge and a desire to push the boundaries of human capability.  From the earliest astronomical observations to the latest robotic missions, we have sought to understand our place in the cosmos.  But what are the ethical considerations of venturing further into space?  Should we prioritize exploring other planets over addressing pressing issues here on Earth?",
          "question": "Do you think the benefits of space exploration outweigh the costs, and what are the ethical implications of exploring and potentially colonizing other planets?",
          "imagePrompt": "A split image: one side showing a lush, green Earth, and the other side showing a barren, red Mars. No text or words should appear in the image."
        },
        {
          "paragraphContext": "The challenges of space travel are immense, requiring cutting-edge technology and incredible human resilience.  From the extreme temperatures and radiation of space to the psychological effects of isolation and confinement, astronauts face numerous obstacles.  What qualities and skills do you think are essential for someone embarking on a journey into the unknown?",
          "question": "What are the biggest challenges of space travel, and what kind of person do you think makes a good astronaut?",
          "imagePrompt": "An astronaut inside a spacecraft, looking out a window at the Earth, with a contemplative expression on their face. No text or words should appear in the image."
        },
        {
          "paragraphContext": "The discovery of extraterrestrial life would be one of the most significant events in human history, potentially reshaping our understanding of biology, philosophy, and religion.  But how would we react to such a discovery?  Would we embrace our cosmic neighbors, or would we view them with suspicion and fear?",
          "question": "How do you think humanity would react to the discovery of alien life, and what impact would it have on our world?",
          "imagePrompt": "A scientist in a lab looking through a microscope at a strange, otherworldly organism, with a look of surprise on their face. No text or words should appear in the image."
        },
        {
          "paragraphContext": "The vastness of space is almost incomprehensible, with billions of galaxies, each containing billions of stars.  The sheer scale of the universe can be both awe-inspiring and humbling.  It makes you wonder: are we truly alone in this cosmic ocean, or are there other intelligent civilizations out there, waiting to be discovered?",
          "question": "Do you believe there is life beyond Earth, and why or why not?",
          "imagePrompt": "A vast, starry sky filled with galaxies and nebulae, suggesting the immensity of the universe. No text or words should appear in the image."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "quiz",
      "title": "Knowledge Check",
      "questions": [
        {
          "question": "What does 'orbit' mean?",
          "options": ["To launch a rocket", "The path of an object around a celestial body", "A type of spacecraft", "A spacesuit"],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "'Orbit' refers to the curved path an object takes around a planet, star, or moon."
        },
        {
          "question": "What is an 'astronaut'?",
          "options": ["A type of rocket", "A person who travels in space", "A planet", "A star"],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "An 'astronaut' is a person trained to travel in space."
        },
        {
          "question": "What does 'launch' mean in the context of space travel?",
          "options": ["To land a spacecraft", "To send something into space", "To orbit a planet", "To explore a new planet"],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "'Launch' means to send something, like a rocket or spacecraft, into space."
        },
        {
          "question": "Is 'exploration' the act of discovering new places?",
          "options": ["True", "False"],
          "answer": "True",
          "explanation": "'Exploration' involves traveling to and learning about unfamiliar areas."
        },
        {
          "question": "Does 'technology' only refer to computers?",
          "options": ["True", "False"],
          "answer": "False",
          "explanation": "'Technology' is the application of scientific knowledge for practical purposes, encompassing a wide range of tools and techniques."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
